# Web-v2 Chat Route Architecture

`apps/web-v2/app/api/chat/route.ts` is **2,989 lines** — the single biggest file in the codebase and the central nervous system for every chat turn. This rule documents its phase structure, the AI SDK v6 conventions it uses, and the HITL resume protocol that lives inline in the same POST handler post-v0.7e Phase 5.

Re-read before:
- Modifying any phase of the chat request lifecycle.
- Adding a new pre-stream concern (auth, rate-limit, telemetry, context block).
- Touching the engine ↔ AI SDK Agent bridge.
- Reasoning about why something happens "in the chat route" vs. somewhere else.

## The phase map

POST `/api/chat` runs these phases in order. Line numbers are approximate (drift with edits) — use the section headers `// ---` in the file as anchors.

| # | Phase | What happens | Key calls |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Auth | Header-based zkLogin; rejects 401 if missing/invalid | `getCurrentUser()` (`lib/audric-auth.ts`) — reads `x-zklogin-jwt` |
| 2 | Rate limit | 20 req/min per IP for the engine surface | `rateLimit('engine:${ip}', 20, 60_000)` |
| 3 | Pre-warm | Fire-and-forget portfolio prefetch (60s in-process cache primes) | `prewarmPortfolio(walletAddress)` |
| 4 | Body parse | Accepts BOTH `UIMessage` shape (from `useChat`) AND legacy `{role, content}` shape (curl/smoke) | `bodySchema.parse()` (zod union) |
| 5 | Chat row | Lazy-upsert deferred to `saveMessages` (P1-E); ownership check still runs here for non-new chats | `getChatRowById({ chatId })` |
| 6 | Resume extraction | Pulls outcomes from prior `tool-approval-response` parts in `body.messages` for `attemptId` round-trip | `extractResumeOutcomes(body.messages)` |
| 7 | Telemetry init | Single `TelemetryIntegration` instance per request — owns TurnMetrics + SessionUsage writes | `new TelemetryIntegration()` |
| 8 | Model edge | Vercel AI Gateway via `gateway('anthropic/<model>')`; wrapped with `wrapLanguageModel` for observability | `gateway('anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6')` |
| 9 | Context blocks | Advice context folds into the static `instructions` (NOT prepareStep). The `<financial_context>` block was retired in S.375 — the agent orients via read tools. | `buildAdviceContext(...)` + `buildAudricSystemPrompt({...})` |
| 10 | Memory wiring | `prepareStep` callback for per-turn `<memory_recall>` injection; `onFinish` callback for post-turn MemWal write | `buildMemoryPrepareStep({...})` + `buildMemoryWriteCallback({...})` |
| 11 | Title generation | Background `generateChatTitle({...})` for new chats — fire-and-forget, races `saveMessages` teardown but is upsert-safe | `generateChatTitle({...})` |
| 12 | Agent construction | AI SDK v6 `Experimental_Agent` with engine tools (via `toAISDKTools`), system instructions, `prepareStep`, `onFinish`, `experimental_telemetry`, `experimental_context` | `new Agent({ model, tools, instructions, prepareStep, onFinish, ... })` |
| 13 | Message conversion | UI `parts[]` → canonical `ModelMessage[]` with tool-call/result/approval pairs intact | `convertToModelMessages(uiMessages)` |
| 14 | Stream | Engine stream consumed and translated to `UIMessage` parts via the `createUIMessageStream` writer | `audricAgent.stream({ messages })` + `createUIMessageStream({ execute })` |
| 15 | Persist | `onFinish` of `createUIMessageStream` upserts messages + lazy-upserts Chat row + bumps `updatedAt` | `saveMessages({ skipDuplicates: true })` |
| 16 | Return | AI SDK v6 streaming Response | `createUIMessageStreamResponse({ stream })` |

`maxDuration = 300` (S.212 / 2026-05-21). Don't lower it — adaptive thinking on Tier 2/3 prompts genuinely produces 40–60s reasoning spans.

## Engine bridge — how `@t2000/engine` plugs in

Web-v2 does NOT call `engine.submitMessage()`. It uses AI SDK v6's `Experimental_Agent` DIRECTLY, with engine TOOLS adapted via `toAISDKTools()`.

```typescript
import {
  applyToolFlags,
  classifyEffort,
  composeBundleFromToolResults,
  DEFAULT_GUARD_CONFIG,
  DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CONFIG,
  getModifiableFields,
  getToolPolicy,
  toAISDKTools,
  type Tool,
  type ToolContext,
} from '@t2000/engine';
import { Experimental_Agent as Agent } from 'ai';

const aiSdkTools = toAISDKTools(engineTools, toolContext);
const agent = new Agent({ model, tools: aiSdkTools, instructions, prepareStep, onFinish });
```

The engine is consumed as **policy + tool definitions**, not as a runtime. Guards, permission resolution, modifiable-field extraction, and bundle composition all run in this route via the engine's exported helpers (`DEFAULT_GUARD_CONFIG`, `DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CONFIG`, `getToolPolicy`, `getModifiableFields`, `composeBundleFromToolResults`). The `Agent` class drives the LLM loop.

## AI SDK v6 wire format conventions

| Concept | v6 (canonical) | v3 (banned) |
|---|---|---|
| Streaming response | `createUIMessageStreamResponse({ stream })` | `createDataStreamResponse(...)` |
| Stream writer | `createUIMessageStream({ execute })` | `createDataStream(...)` |
| Message shape | `UIMessage` with `parts: UIMessagePart[]` | `Message` with `content: string` |
| Client hook | `useChat({ transport: DefaultChatTransport })` | `useChat({ api: '/api/chat' })` |
| LLM driver | `Experimental_Agent` from `'ai'` | `streamText` / `generateText` standalone |
| Tool conversion | `toAISDKTools(engineTools)` from `@t2000/engine` | manual schema mapping |
| Provider edge | `gateway('anthropic/<model>')` from `'ai'` | `createAnthropic(...)` direct |
| Per-turn system | `prepareStep` callback returning `{ system }` | static `system` prop only |
| Custom UI parts | `data-<name>` typed parts via the writer | bespoke event schema |

The Vercel AI Gateway proxy (`gateway` from `'ai'`) is the canonical model edge. `@ai-sdk/anthropic`'s `createAnthropic` is imported but should only be used for tests / fallbacks, never in the live request path.

## The Audric bundle marker (Phase 5e custom data part)

When the LLM produces ≥2 confirm-tier bundleable writes in one step, the route emits ONE `data-audric-bundle` UIMessageStream part at the `finish-step` boundary. The client renders ONE PermissionCard for the bundle (instead of N cards), dispatches ONE sponsored bundle PTB, then fans out N `addToolApprovalResponse` + N `addToolOutput` calls so AI SDK's state machine sees individual resolutions.

```typescript
// From route.ts ~line 220
const BUNDLE_MARKER_TYPE = 'data-audric-bundle' as const;
export interface AudricBundleMarker {
  steps: Array<{
    toolCallId: string;
    approvalId: string;       // [agent-harness-spec.mdc §3a] mirrors attemptId
    toolName: string;
    input: Record<string, unknown>;
    description: string;
    modifiableFields: Array<{ name: string; kind: string; asset?: string }>;
  }>;
}
```

The `approvalId === attemptId` invariant is load-bearing for `TurnMetrics` resume keying — see `agent-harness-spec.mdc` Item 3 + Item 3a.

## HITL resume protocol — INLINE in this same route

Pre-v0.7e Phase 5 there was a separate `/api/engine/resume` route. **It's gone.** The resume turn re-enters this same `POST /api/chat` handler:

1. User taps Confirm on a `tool-approval-request` part → client signs & executes the sponsored tx → client calls `addToolApprovalResponse({ approvalId, ... })` + `addToolOutput({ toolCallId, ... })`.
2. `useChat` immediately fires the next request with the message history augmented with the approval/output parts.
3. This route hits Phase 6 (`extractResumeOutcomes`), pulls the prior `tool-approval-response` parts, and builds a Prisma `updateMany` keyed on `attemptId` to stamp `pendingActionOutcome` + `writeToolDurationMs` on the originating `TurnMetrics` row.
4. The same Agent loop continues from where it paused, narrating the post-write turn.

`extractResumeOutcomes` returning a non-empty array is the signal that "this is a resume turn." See `write-tool-pending-action.mdc` for the full 6-step contract.

## What's banned

```typescript
// ❌ Reaching for v3 idioms
import { streamText, createDataStreamResponse } from 'ai'; // wrong response builder
import type { Message } from 'ai/react';                    // wrong message type

// ✅ v6 canonical
import { Experimental_Agent as Agent, createUIMessageStream, createUIMessageStreamResponse, type UIMessage } from 'ai';
```

```typescript
// ❌ Bypassing the AI Gateway in the live request path
import { createAnthropic } from '@ai-sdk/anthropic';
const anthropic = createAnthropic({ apiKey: env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY });
const model = anthropic('claude-sonnet-4-6'); // direct provider — bypasses gateway observability + retries

// ✅ Through the gateway
import { gateway } from 'ai';
const model = gateway('anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6');
```

```typescript
// ❌ Adding a new "/api/engine/something" route in parallel
// app/api/engine/foo/route.ts ← STOP. There is no engine route surface in web-v2.
// Every chat-side concern lives in /api/chat/route.ts (resume, post-write, telemetry inline).
```

```typescript
// ❌ Calling engine.submitMessage() from web-v2
import { AISDKEngine } from '@t2000/engine';
const engine = new AISDKEngine({...});
await engine.submitMessage(...); // Web-v2 doesn't drive the engine like this; it composes Agent directly.

// ✅ Use the engine's exports as policy + tools
import { toAISDKTools, getToolPolicy, DEFAULT_GUARD_CONFIG } from '@t2000/engine';
import { Experimental_Agent as Agent } from 'ai';
const agent = new Agent({ model, tools: toAISDKTools(engineTools, ctx), instructions, ... });
```

```typescript
// ❌ Static system that tries to inject memory
const instructions = `${baseSystem}\n\n${memoryBlock}`; // memory MUST come from prepareStep, not the static system

// ✅ Per-turn memory injection
const audricAgent = new Agent({
  instructions: buildAudricSystemPrompt({ ... }), // static (includes advice; no financial_context post-S.375)
  prepareStep: buildMemoryPrepareStep({ ... }),   // dynamic (memory recall per turn)
  onFinish: buildMemoryWriteCallback({ ... }),    // dynamic (memory write post-turn)
});
```

```typescript
// ❌ Lowering maxDuration
export const maxDuration = 60; // S.212 lesson: adaptive thinking can take 40–60s on Tier 2/3 prompts

// ✅ Match the proven legacy ceiling
export const maxDuration = 300;
```

## Adding a new pre-stream phase

If you genuinely need to add a phase (rare — most concerns belong in helpers, not the route):

1. Insert it in the right slot per the phase map above. Auth-adjacent concerns go between phase 1 and 2; context-block additions go in phase 9; telemetry side-effects go in phase 7.
2. If it's I/O, weigh fire-and-forget vs. blocking. The route's `prewarmPortfolio` (phase 3) and `generateChatTitle` (phase 11) are the canonical fire-and-forget patterns. Use `waitUntil()` from `@vercel/functions` to keep the streaming response flushing while the background work completes.
3. If it returns a context block to feed the LLM, decide whether it's static (fold into `buildAudricSystemPrompt` / phase 9) or per-turn (extend `prepareStep` / phase 10). Static is cheaper.
4. Audit downstream — `extractResumeOutcomes` consumes the message history; new shapes must round-trip without data loss.

